## 📖 Overview

This project presents a **Smart Traffic Control System** that replaces traditional fixed-time traffic signals with an adaptive, AI-driven approach.

| Component | Technology |
|-----------|------------|
| Camera Module | ESP32-CAM |
| AI Model | YOLOv8 |
| Processing | Python |
| Signal Controller | Arduino Mega |

---

## ❗ Problem Statement

Traditional traffic systems suffer from several critical limitations:

- ⏱️ Use **fixed timers** regardless of actual traffic volume
- 🚗 **Ignore real-time** traffic density and conditions
- 🔴 Cause unnecessary **congestion and delays**
- 🚑 **Cannot prioritize** emergency vehicles efficiently

---

## 💡 Proposed Solution

A hybrid system that intelligently adapts to real-world traffic conditions:

- 🤖 Detects and counts vehicles using AI (YOLOv8)
- 📊 Adjusts signal timing dynamically per lane
- 🔄 Supports both static (fallback) and dynamic (AI) modes
- 🚑 Provides emergency vehicle priority override

---

